body:
@drpngx @asimshankar, 
I am not sure about removing `convert_image_dtype` from these decode functions, because `decode_png` will return uint16 tensor, and other decode functions always return uint8s. 
In function `tf.image.decode_image`, `tf.cond` is used to check image format, but it is unsupported with different input data type.
